itemListElement.name: Stevens Pass Ski Resort Tour from Seattle

name: Stevens Pass Ski Resort Tour from Seattle
description:
Experience the ultimate ski adventure with our Steven’s Pass Ski resort Transportation & sightseeing tour. We offer pick-up services from hotels and accommodations in Downtown Seattle, Bellevue, Kirkland & Bothell, so you don’t have to worry about transportation. Our experienced guides will take you on a tour of the resort and show you the best slopes and breathtaking views. You’ll get to experience the stunning natural beauty of the Cascade Mountains and the breathtaking views of the Pacific Northwest. Our guides will take you on a tour of the area and show you the best spots for sightseeing and photography. 
In addition, our driver guide would be flexible to give you ride to Nordic Center.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Waterfront Tour in Comfy Mercedes ... Awesome Sites ;-)

name: Seattle Waterfront Tour in Comfy Mercedes ... Awesome Sites ;-)
description:
Relax in a classic Mercedes for a comfy and personal tour guided by me, a Northwest native and former Seattle Times reporter. 

Enjoy a visit to Shilshole Bay Marina and Seattle's Golden Gardens Park. Take in the beauty of Puget Sound and the Olympic Mountains from Sunset Hill Park. We'll visit the famous and much-beloved Hiram M. Chittenden Locks (which raise vessels from salt water up to lake level) and take a behind-the-scenes tour of Fishermen's Terminal, where much of the Alaska fishing fleet home ports--including many of the vessels from "Deadliest Catch." We'll also visit beautiful Green Lake, designed by the same Olmsted Brothers who designed Central Park, and see some of Seattle's original houseboats from back in the day of their Bohemian glory.

itemListElement.name: Full Day Leavenworth and Cascade Mountain Adventure Tour

name: Full Day Leavenworth and Cascade Mountain Adventure Tour
description:
Join us on a journey to the famous Bavarian town of Leavenworth, tucked among the Cascade Mountains and blanketed in the winter spirit with thousands of holiday lights, eternal Christmas Stores, snow frosted trees, and more! It's something that you just have to experience for yourself.

This full day tour begins in Seattle and travels east through Snoqualmie Pass where you will stop to enjoy warm drinks and a hike or snowshoe walk along a level forested trail. The total walk will be 1-2.5 miles depending on the day.

As you continue, notice how the landscape changes from west to east side of the Cascade Mountains. Washington is often thought of as the rainy state, but you'll soon notice the air seems drier! Most of the east side receives between 5-25 in. of precipitation annually (making for a great winter escape!)

In Leavenworth, you have time in town on your own. Experience authentic Bavarian foods, shop around the artisan stores, or wander through the festive streets of downtown.

review.name: Awesome snowy Christmas experience!
review.reviewBody: The whole tour was awesome. Our guide Karen had so much local knowledge and took the time to allow us to stop and see the snow - a novelty for us Aussies. Leavenworth was everything we hoped with snow on the ground and everything. Thankyou Karen for being such an awesome guide and the gluten free snacks were very appreciated and delicious!! As was the hot coffee and tea on the hike!!!

name: Seattle Premium Fitness Pass
description:
Are you an avid gym-goer who wants to maintain your fitness routine while traveling? Look no further than the Premium Fitness Pass - Seattle!

With this pass, you can access the top gyms across the city with no time restrictions, so you can work out at your convenience. itemListElement.name: Seattle Holiday Donut Adventure & Walking Food Tour

name: Seattle Holiday Donut Adventure & Walking Food Tour
description:
Satisfy your sweet tooth during your visit to Seattle on a donut-themed holiday tour. Be sure to arrive with an empty stomach, as this culinary experience includes visits to four of the city’s top bakeries, where you will try holiday-themed flavors,learn about the donut-making process and traditions of each location, and stroll next to the Pike Place Market giant holiday tree and festive decorations while sipping Columbian hot cocoa.

• Enjoy a small tour group size of a maximum of 15 people
• Take a Seattle culinary tour that the whole family can enjoy
• Enjoy donuts at Seattle’s top bakeries in around two hours
• Choose a start time that suits your vacation schedule

review.name: Lots of fun and tasty, tasty desserts
review.reviewBody: The underground doughnut tour is always a lot of fun and very tasty. Athina was an absolutely great guide telling us a lot about the history of Seattle while keeping feeding us very tasty doughnuts as we walked the city.

review.name: Sweet!
review.reviewBody: Nice tour with Athina! We all had lots of fun while tasting delicious donuts and yummy hot chocolate. It's was a very enjoyable experience.

review.name: Fun tour
review.reviewBody: Really fun walking tour with great donuts. Athina was great and gave some fun Seattle facts along the way. Would definitely do this again.

review.name: Delicious!
review.reviewBody: Athena was a blast and extremely knowledgeable. All the stops were amazing, even though it was slightly raining through the tour. Can't recommend the Underground Donut Tour enough!

review.name: Great tasty tour
review.reviewBody: Awesome tour with Athina. Learned a lot and the donuts were awesome. My favorite was the Tres leches at doce donuts. Highly recommended.

review.name: Donut Tour
review.reviewBody: Awesome tour, guide was knowledgeable and fun. The donuts were delicious. Even on a rainy day this is a good tour. Athena our guide really knew her stuff.

review.name: Top tier
review.reviewBody: Athena best tour guide I could ask for. Top tier. First time in Seattle and love it out here. Athena has great knowledge of the city and the donut tour.

review.name: Awesome!
review.reviewBody: What a great way to experience Seattle’s unique donut scene! We had such a great time on the holiday tour, even in the pouring rain! Deb’s enthusiasm was infectious and we had so much fun gorging on donuts and learning interesting facts about Seattle. I recommend this tour not only to people visiting from out of town, but locals too. It’s fun to view your own city through the lens of a donut tour.

review.name: A fun way to see Seattle landmarks and enjoy delicious donuts
review.reviewBody: We had a fun tour with Bella. The donuts were tasty, and Bella gave us information about some Seattle buildings and landmarks that we had not known about before. The donut selection was a nice mix. Our favorites were the Tres Leches donut and the Lemon donut - but all were yummy. It was rainy and windy for part of the tour, but it's Seattle, right?

itemListElement.name: Guided Seattle Holiday Lights Tour with Santa Photo Op

name: Guided Seattle Holiday Lights Tour with Santa Photo Op
description: Remember piling into the car and cruising the neighborhoods to find the best holiday lights? Join Show Me Seattle on an excursion to discover Seattle’s holiday sparkle…enjoy visits to the best light displays, hear fun stories of Seattle holidays past and finish the trip with a visit to Santa for a picture perfect photo op. We'll see the magical lights in Pioneer Square, Downtown Seattle, The Seattle Waterfront and more on our way to West Seattle for some of the most spectacular private home displays in the city. Then back to visit Santa! Come dressed in your best and don't forget your camera phone - this is the chance to grab those perfect photos. Enjoy cocoa and other holiday treats before you bundle up and head back home...create a new family tradition with this one of a kind experience.

review.name: Seattle Light Tour was a big hit!
review.reviewBody: The tour of Seattle's Holiday lights was absolutely a hit with my toddler and myself! I got a chance to relax and let someone else do the driving while we enjoyed the lights. Everyone was so nice and seeing Santa when we were done was a special treat! It was a jolly evening and we'll be back next year!

review.name: Best way to see Seattle holiday lights
review.reviewBody: Such a fun way to see the holiday lights. Seattle has beautiful light displays and this tour company knew just where to take us. Tour guide Elvis and his helper Spencer were entertaining and full of Seattle trivia. I took my mother and two young adult kids, it was a fun family outing!
